New World Resources Plc (NWR) , the biggest
Czech producer of coking coal, rose for a third day in  Prague  as
demand for commodities increased.  The stock added 3.1 percent to 101 koruna by 10:38 a.m.
local time, paring its weekly decline to 1 percent. New World
was the second-best performer today in the 14-member  PX (PX)  equity
index, which advanced 0.6 percent.  Global stocks and commodities rose on optimism that central
banks may step up economic stimulus. Europeâ€™s benchmark coal
derivatives climbed 0.8 percent to $96.90 a metric ton in the
Netherlands, after reaching a two-year low of $95.25 on June 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
